This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses ensemble methods and distillation. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing intelligent systems for language understanding. The use of LSTM networks and structured hinge loss objective also suggests a possible categorization under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's mention of parsing Chinese and German languages may indicate a potential categorization under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) for cross-lingual natural language processing.
